Sentencas: SmBaMn2O5+delta (SBMO), a novel layered perovskite compound with samarium based material (Sm+3) as rare earth doped in A-site was synthesized and processed by using dry chemistry method (solid state solution).
Titulo: Novel layered perovskite SmBaMn2O5+δ for SOFCs anode material

Sentencas: Structural characterization of SBMO has been investigated by X-ray diffraction (XRD) and scanning electron microscopy (SEM).
Titulo: Novel layered perovskite SmBaMn2O5+δ for SOFCs anode material

Sentencas: While, thermal and electrochemical testing were done by using thermo-gravimetric analysis (TGA) and current voltage measurements.
Titulo: Novel layered perovskite SmBaMn2O5+δ for SOFCs anode material

Sentencas: The Rietveld analysis of XRD data shows that SBMO was crystallized in the orthorhombic structure with the Pmmm space group.
Titulo: Novel layered perovskite SmBaMn2O5+δ for SOFCs anode material

Sentencas: The surface morphology images showed a porous structure which indicates that this material can be used as a potential electrode in solid oxide fuel cells (SOFCs).
Titulo: Novel layered perovskite SmBaMn2O5+δ for SOFCs anode material

Sentencas: TGA result showed the mass loss of 0.022% for SmBaMn2O5+delta which is very small and indicates that the material is very stable.
Titulo: Novel layered perovskite SmBaMn2O5+δ for SOFCs anode material

Sentencas: DC conductivity and performance test were done at RT in air atmosphere.
Titulo: Novel layered perovskite SmBaMn2O5+δ for SOFCs anode material

Sentencas: The performance tests have done at 800 degrees C and 750 degrees C and the maximum power density was found to be 0.4 W/cm(2) at 800 degrees C. (C) 2017
Titulo: Novel layered perovskite SmBaMn2O5+δ for SOFCs anode material
